---\n### Professional Design and Enhancement for `index.html` Page\n\nThis pull request transforms the existing skeletal `index.html` into a modern, professional, and responsive webpage focused on delivering an optimal user experience for PCVR audiences. The updated design aligns with contemporary web standards, while maintaining simplicity, modularity, and scalability.\n---\n#### **Key Updates**\n1. **Semantic Structure**\n   - Clean, well-organized HTML5 tags including `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, and `<footer>`.\n   - Easily navigable page structure for a seamless browsing experience.\n\n2. **SEO and Metadata Optimization**\n   - Included essential `<meta>` tags for better search engine visibility, optimized keywords, and responsive scaling.\n\n3. **Rich Content Sections**\n   - **Navigation Bar:** Sticky nav design with placeholder links (e.g., Features, Dashboard, Pools, About, Contact).\n   - **Hero Section:** Eye-catching headline, concise subtext, and dual call-to-action buttons.\n   - **Feature Highlights:** Four custom cards derived from existing dashboard features (e.g., Global Statistics, Wallet Info, Active Orders).\n   - **Footer:** Organized into Quick Links and Contact sections, ensuring easy access to additional resources.\n\n4. **PCVR-Centered Styling**\n   - Sleek, dark theme with contrasting blue/green accent colors to align with PCVR's aesthetic.\n   - Fully inline CSS – ensuring quick loading times without external dependencies.\n   - Responsiveness: Expertly configured for all screen sizes, with breakpoints at 768px and 480px.\n---\n#### **Design Goals**\n- Create an immersive yet high-performing webpage tailored to PCVR users.\n- Lay the groundwork for future design modularity.\n- Focus on accessibility, usability, and performance.\n---\n**This pull request not only enhances the aesthetic appeal but further solidifies the web standard readiness for rich cross-platform user engagement.** Feedback and collaboration are welcome!